Your biggest obstacle now is time managment; and the trick with these hare engineering majors is that you cannot be absolute in all your deadlines. You need to sit down and develop backup plans and fail safes. For example: you have to turn in homework problems or do online module. If you run out of time, then you can only do half of them and get half of the points. Thins like that, so you don't end up breaking down and fail everything; thus, it is essential to look at the syllubus to see where you can loose points and where you can lax on studying as last resorts. Don't ever spend more time than you need to trying to get a perfect grade. I wasted 3 weeks on nothing but a heat exchange design problem, a project that was only worth like 10-20% of the class grade.
